  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Smart Classrooms for children with Autism</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Fund for Keshatot Children, supports Keshatot, Harim and Dror schools for Autistic children in Israel. Half of the children do not speak. We continue to fund iPads, AppleTvs, apps, repairs and up-grades for iPads and smart boards in every school and kindergarten classroom. This year the Fund wishes to purchase 10 additional iPads equipped with the TouchChat App, especially strong and shock-resistant protective cases suitable, and another 2 TV screens and Apple TVs to be used with the iPads.</narrative>
  </description>
